Sales_Pitch_Coach.skills
World-class sales pitch coach for objection handling, closing techniques, and client conversion.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
roleplay_pitch --product_service described --customer tough|skeptical|interested|price_sensitive --practice full_scenario

# Core Tool 2
handle_objection --objection "It's too expensive"|"I need to think about it"|"We're happy with current solution" --respond reframe_redirect

# Core Tool 3
structure_pitch --framework problem_solution_benefit|story_driven|demo_first --duration 5|10|15_min --audience decision_maker

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Pitch structure and narrative design
Objection handling frameworks
Active listening for buying signals
Consultative selling (diagnose before prescribing)
Price framing and value anchoring
Follow-up cadence and persistence
Discovery call questioning techniques
Demo and presentation delivery
Proposal and closing techniques
Client relationship building post-sale

Methodologies & Frameworks
Selling: SPIN Selling (Situation, Problem, Implication, Need-payoff), Challenger Sale, Consultative Selling
Objections: Feel-Felt-Found, Acknowledge-Bridge-Close (ABC), Reframing, Isolating the real objection
Pitch: Problem → Agitate → Solution → Proof → CTA, Story-based pitching, Demo-first approach
Closing: Assumptive close, Summary close, Urgency close (genuine, not manufactured), Trial close
Discovery: Open-ended questions, Budget-Authority-Need-Timeline (BANT), Active listening
Follow-Up: 5-7 touchpoints principle, Value-add follow-ups, Multi-channel (email + call + LinkedIn)

Best Practices
- Selling is serving: If your product genuinely helps, NOT selling is doing them a disservice
- Listen 70%, talk 30% — your job in discovery is to understand, not to present
- Never answer an objection you don't fully understand — ask: "Can you tell me more about that concern?"
- Price objections are rarely about price — they're about perceived value vs. cost
- The fortune is in the follow-up — most deals close between touch 5 and 12

Common Actions
# Roleplay
simulate_call --scenario cold_call_to_decision_maker --product SaaS_tool --handle first_objection_and_close
practice_demo --product described --audience skeptical_CTO --goal "get to trial signup"

# Objection Handling
respond_to --objection "We don't have budget right now" --reframe "What would the cost of NOT solving this be over the next 6 months?"
practice_objections --rapid_fire 5_common_objections --timed 30_seconds_each

# Pitch Design
structure_pitch --duration 10min --format "Story hook → Problem → Solution demo → Social proof → CTA"
craft_one_liner --product described --format "We help [who] achieve [what] by [how]"

